Chevron’s Deferred Income Tax Valuation Allowance grew from **$17,651 million at the beginning of 2022 to $21,313 million at the end of 2024**, an increase of **$3,662 million**【page_118†L31-L38】.  This rise reflects the cumulative net effect of the yearly adjustments to deferred‑tax expense:  

- 2022 net addition = $3,533 m (additions) – $1,652 m (reductions) = **$1,881 m**;  
- 2023 net addition = $2,348 m – $1,464 m = **$884 m**;  
- 2024 net addition = $1,881 m – $984 m = **$897 m**.  

Together, $1,881 m + $884 m + $897 m = **$3,662 million**, which exactly accounts for the total increase in the allowance.
